definition: nothing to pick on/really good/nothing to discuss/settled matter/no problem
to speak/to say/to explain/to scold/to tell off/a theory (typically the last character in a compound, as in 日心說|日心说 heliocentric theory)
of/~'s (possessive particle)/(used after an attribute)/(used to form a nominal expression)/(used at the end of a declarative sentence for emphasis)

sentences.english: The interior decoration of this house is really good.
sentences.chinese: 這戶人家的室內裝修真是沒說的。

sentences.english: What you don't say is perhaps the alter ego of what you say.
sentences.chinese: 你沒說的可能是你所說的東西的“另一個自我”。

sentences.english: If you are any sensible, you can predict these unsaid things.
sentences.chinese: 如果你是任何明智的，你能預測這些沒說的事情。

sentences.english: To seek whatever you want but never told me.
The bridal chamber is sumptuously decorated.
sentences.chinese: 這戶人家的室內裝修真是沒說的。

sentences.english: We can always add a sentence we did not say.
sentences.chinese: 我們總有機會補充一句沒說的話。
